race.comment: NOR NOR WEST (1) went back from a wide draw last start over 1000m at Muswellbrook and struggled to get involved. That run followed an eight-week let-up so he will strip fitter. Better placed out to 1200m and in an inferior race he looks ready to win again. BEAUTY EDGE (2) appreciated the drop in grade when a closing third last Saturday over 1100m at Forbes. At his best over today's trip, with a 75% top-three strike rate. Big threat out of the inside gate on a quick turnaround. CHAMP DE MARS (5) hasn't won for 60 weeks but gets her chance. Fair effort last time over today's trip at Canberra, with a 4.5 kg drop in weight bringing her right into contention. HARD TOO IMPRESS (3) has been a bit plain of late but it is worth noting he has raced here three times for three minor placings, including once at this distance. Can turn things around. Lightly raced mare DIG BEE (4) is fitter for two runs back from a spell and won't find this as tough.
